{
  "texts": [
    "We can imagine someone encountering the man pumping water and asking what he is up to.",
    "The formal order in action is given by the sincere answers that the man would give to iterations of the question 'Why?'.",
    "Following Wiesman (2016, p. 126), we can lay these out like this: Notice that the series (A)-(D) gives different descriptions of an action while in (E) yet another action description (of the poisoning as a killing) provides the antecedent of a conditional claim, of which the consequent is a desirable state of affairs (that we will get a better government).",
    "Notice also that, if we reformulate the action descrip-1 3 tion in (E) as (E*): I am killing the inhabitants, and (E**): I am getting a better government, the series (A)-(E**) can be reversed so that each item in the reversed series (E**)-(A) could be given in answer to a 'how?'",
    "question asked of its predecessor."
  ]
}